persons <- persons %>%

                          (as.Date(ymd(20170101)),

                         ) %>%

#making IR with 95% CI 
IR_95_CI <- function(events, py, N){
  tmp <- as.matrix(cbind(events, py))
  conf_ints <- round(epi.conf(tmp, ctype = "inc.rate", method = "exact", N = N, design = 1, 
   conf.level = 0.95) * 1000, 2)
  return(conf_ints)
}

Ulm K (1990). A simple method to calculate the confidence interval of a standardized mortality ratio. American Journal of Epidemiology 131: 373 - 375

make_year_age_bands <- function(data, age_group) {
  new_data <- data %>% 
    filter(age_bands==age_group) 
  return(new_data)
  }

# Make function to calculate amount of events
amount_events <- function(data, diagn) {
  events <- data %>% 
    filter(Diagnosis == diagn) %>%  nrow()
  return(events)
}

Forest Plots

Total

library(tidyverse)

df <- Big_table 



df_total <- df %>%  
  filter(Year=='Total')

df_total$y_order <- factor(paste(df_total$Diagnosis, df_total$Age_Bands, sep = " - "), levels = unique(paste(df_total$Diagnosis, df_total$Age_Bands, sep = " - ")), ordered = TRUE)
# plot the forest plot
ggplot(df_total, aes(x = IR_1000_PY, y = y_order)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_errorbarh(aes(xmin = IR_1000_PY_95L, xmax = IR_1000PY_95H)) +
  facet_grid(Diagnosis ~ ., scales = "free_y", space = "free_y") +
  theme_bw() +
  labs(title = "Forest Plot of Incidence Rates",
       x = "Incidence Rate per 1000 Person-Years",
       y = "Diagnosis and Age Band",
       subtitle = "Data from 2017 to 2020")
